BRIEFLY 
Retail Sales Rise in July: Most of the nation's big retailers reported modest 
July sales gains, but analysts said the upcoming back-to-school and fall season 
would better reflect how consumers are reacting to rising oil prices and a 
weakening economy. Wal-Mart Stores Inc., the nation's third-largest retailer, 
posted a 21% sales gain in July, to $2.4 billion from $1.98 billion a year 
earlier. 
The weakest results were seen at general merchandise retailers such as Sears, 
Roebuck &amp; Co., the nation's biggest retailer, and K mart Corp., said Janet 
Mangano, an analyst at Jesup, Josephthal &amp; Co. The Sears merchandise Group 
said July sales from continuing operations rose 3.7% to $2.52 billion, from 
$2.43 billion a year ago. 
